<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="218" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="15" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,151,176]" pageId="15" pageNumber="218">Comments</emphasis>
. The species is characterized by the yellow colour of the pleural sclerites, three dark stripes on the scutum, long flagellomeres, a prolonged and bulbous gonostylus without a tooth and with 4 apical spines. It belongs to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Winnertz" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[315,419,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilaris">
<emphasis box="[315,419,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="218">B. hilaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, although the necks are not bicoloured.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
